posts.cooked: because we are new to the Java game. The directions to us aren’t 100 clear. it looks like it goes in then drive subsystem but then comments store in your constants file. Where does this actually go in our code?

posts.name: Jeffords
posts.cooked: Yes the config method goes in your drive subsystem. The constant file it refers to a file that is generated by the pathplanner app you just need to set the values in the pathplanner app. I think you can also set all of the configs in code but the GUI method is much easier.

posts.name: Owen Tharp
posts.cooked:
Few recommendations I could make in general, I would switch to Elastic instead of the default Dashboard. It is generally easier to understand especially for newer teams. As for this problem, it seems you created an autoChooser before you created the autoBuilder itself. I believe the fix is to add the line “configureAutoBuilder()” in between line 76 and 77 in driveSubsystem Lines 76-77 as seen here 831×503 12.9 KB

Lines 76-77 as seen here 831×503 12.9 KB

Lines 76-77 as seen here 831×503 12.9 KB

posts.name: Owen Tharp
posts.cooked: I think the problem you are running in to is that you created the correct code to create the “autoBuilder” but it is never called. You then go to created the chooser for SmartDashboard, but because you never actually created that autoBuilder in the drive code, it has nothing to pull from and create. Hope this helps! If you reply to this if you still run into any issues, I would be happy to help.
